{ Making may for the other rook and starting operations on the queenside. Without this, Black would have secured adequate counterplay or snatched the c-pawn back, depending on White's decision. }
1... Rxc4 2. Qb3 Qc2 3. Rxf5 Qxb3 4. axb3 Rc3 5. Nd4 Nh6 6. R5f3 Re8 7. Ra1 Ng4
8. e4 Rxf3 9. Nxf3 Rxe4 10. Rxa7 Re3 11. Nd4 h5
{ As an example, this should still be a draw  (Rook+Knight Endgames have a vary high drawing rate, even two pawns down: remember this when in dire straits!)  , but Black will have to suffer for it. }
