[SetUp "1"]

{ We will witness Black's superiority on the kingside in the next chapter. Still, Black does not always draw the short stick on the queenside, as these examples show. Light Square Struggle will similarly reassure you. }
1... Rdb8
{ He is targeting the b3-pawn. A trade on b6 would not solve the problem, so White may try }
2. Bc3 bxc5 3. dxc5
{ and now Black could capture on b3 but this would lose a big chunk of his edge. Instead }
3... Be7 4. Be5 Rb7
{ Black can't take on b3 yet due to Nd4, but c5 is still targeted. } 5. Bd6
{ 27.Bd4  Rxb3 } 5... Bf6
{ Now d4 is controlled and Black keeps strong pressure. A maneuver such as Nc7-b5 will help get rid of the annoying d6-bishop. }
*

