1... c6
{ This piece placement is aimed at pushing b5. Usually White is slightly better but it's not so easy to deal with Black's pawn assault, especially since this plan is much rarer than the one based around e5. When meeting an opponent who plays the opening fast and confidently, opting for this formation makes good practical sense, though objectively it is flawed, as White enjoys greater control in the center due to Black's lack of challenge. }
