{ Black is often in charge, but watch out! Overextension is a real risk and if the f5-pawn is targeted, things can become very ugly for the second player!If you so choose, the diagrams can serve as exercises for training your positional judgment.Then the first question will always be: 'Who should be playing on the kingside ?'The second question is the eternal 'How? Who is better and why?'Grandmasters have failed to take the right decision in those games, more than once.So it's an exciting challenge to compare yourself to those chess heroes ! }
