{ The Classical Dutch structure is highly flexible, which also means that bad pieces can suddenly find a purpose. As a general rule Black does better with one knight than two.If you so choose, the diagrams can serve as exercises for training your positional judgement.Then the first question will always be : "Who has the best minor pieces ? Should and can we trade ?"The second question is the eternal "Who is better and why ?"Grandmasters have failed to take the right decision in those games, more than once.So it's an exciting challenge to compare yourself to those chess heroes ! }
1. -- *

