{ What is White's best defence? } 1. Qxg4
{ Attack ! A pretty queen sacrifice that gives positional domination to White. }
1... fxg4 2. Bxa8 Nb6 3. Bg2 Bf5 4. Rad1
{ White has brilliant piece play. Objectively Black may be fine, but in practical terms, I wouldn't ever come around this position: Black has weaknesses everywhere  (d5-d6-a5, central light squares)  while White is very solid. The only solution for Black seems to rely on the levers on both sides with a4 and h5-h4. Still, without an engine by my side I would call this clearly better. }
