{ White takes control. } 1. a3 Na6 2. b4
{ The rest is a model game for White. } 2... Bf6 3. Bb2 Qd7 4. Bxf6 Rxf6 5. Nd3
a4 6. Rac1 Qf7 7. Nf4
{ Just compare the activity on both sides, which all stem from the d5 pawn. }
7... Bc8 8. Rc3 Bd7 9. Rfc1 h6 10. h4 Ra7 11. h5
{ One more White square in the grinder! } 11... Ra8 12. Re3 Kh7 13. Rcc3 Rb8
14. Qd3 Ra8 15. Ng6
{ g4 is coming to tear the last few light squares to shred. } 15... Rxg6 16.
hxg6+ Kxg6 17. Re6+ Kh7 18. g4 c5 19. b5 Nc7 20. gxf5 Nxb5 21. f6+ Kg8 22. Rc4
Re8 23. Rg4 g5 24. Rxe8+ Bxe8 25. Re4 Kf8 26. Re7 Qg6 27. Be4 Qh5 28. Bf3 Qg6
29. Rxe8+ *

