[SetUp "1"]

{ Breakthrough! } 1. d5 exd5
{ 16...e5  17.Nh4  g6  18.f4!  I know, I know, this is the light squares chapter, but a real game of chess is almost never based on a single theme all the way through the analysis. Here Black pays dearly the absence of a dark square bishop. }
2. cxd5 Nxd5 3. Nd4 g6 4. f3 Nef6 5. e4
{ White is grabbing all the space in the world, he is now close to winning. The bishop pair and the greater number of White pieces looking at kingside means that opening up that side will overwhelm Black. }
