{ Black can't act on the kingside. How can he find activity? } 1... axb4 2.
axb4 b5
{ The d5 square is very important when White can't have a pawn on e4. This is not even a sacrifice, both the b4 and b5 pawns will be terribly weak. Every opening is about the small center  (e4-e5-d4-d5)  . Right now Black fully controls d5 while White has d4, e4-e5 being shared. So the position is about the falling b-pawns. }
