[SetUp "1"]

{ This game shows the danger of double-fianchettoing early in the Dutch. } 1.
h4 d5 2. e5 Be7 3. Ng5 Bxg5 4. hxg5
{ This trade is terrible, considering all the holes on the dark squares and consequently the poor nature of the Black light-squared bishop. }
4... c5 5. f4 a5 6. Nf1 Ba6 7. Ne3 Bxd3 8. Qxd3
{ Now Black solved the second problem but it cost time and White will open up both sides methodically. }
8... Qd7 9. g4 c4 10. Qc2 Na6 11. gxf5 exf5
{ Black has no chance of a Nc7-e6 blockade as the queenside gets opened right away. }
12. b3 b5 13. bxc4 bxc4 14. Rb1 Qc6 15. Kf2 Rab8 16. Kg3 Nc7 17. Rxb8 Rxb8 18.
Rb1 Qe8 19. Rxb8 Qxb8 20. Qa4 Qb5 21. Qa3 Qb1 22. Qe7 Nb5 23. e6 h5 24. Qf7+
Kh8 25. Qf8+ Kh7 26. Qh6+ *

