{ With the bishops, Black has to get space inch by inch. } 1... g5 2. Be3 c5 3.
Rxc3 Ba6 { White now can save his c7 pawn with } 4. b4 Bxe2 5. bxc5 Bxf1 6.
cxd6 Bxd6 7. Kxf1 { Black can now respond with } 7... f4 8. Bd4+ Kh7 9. Rc6
fxg3 10. Rxd6 Rxf3 11. hxg3 Rc8 12. Rd7+ Kg6 13. Bxa7 Rf7 14. Rxf7 Kxf7 15. Bb8
Ke6
{ Black puts his king on b7 and covers the kingside with his rook. This is a draw. }
