[SetUp "1"]

{ I already told you in the introduction that a typical transposition into our structure is the Ne4-f5 couple. The Black knight definitely enjoys the ride on that square while White aims a putting a secure pawn there. Still, my opinion is that a superior strategy is to keep a piece such as a knight to emasculate the whole Black effort on the kingside. White fights for the square with his pawns. }
1. Ne1
{ A typical idea. The knight is going to d3, often its best square by controlling f4, e5, c5 and allowing f3 to chase Black's best piece on e4. }
