{ You have studied this book intently and seriously. Or have you ? This is the moment to get some serious feedback on your effort.The exercises have been ranked from oldest to most recent, with no underlying evolution in terms of themes or difficulty. This is done in order to force you to judge the position in the same way as you would in a game.I recommend that before each exercise you assign an amount of time that you think the position is worth at first glance. Once you played a move and looked at the solution, amend or keep that amount to evaluate your decision-making process. Playing a move is not enough: you also need to judge the resulting positions.There is no grade at the end of the test, instead you may come back to it from time to time in order to reassess and refresh your knowledge of the Classical Dutch Structure, in case one  (or two, or three)  iterations were not enough.Different abilities call for different improvements, but I still believe that after completing this test you shall be better armed than 95% of the players that will challenge you in a Classical Dutch structure !  (Provided serious work over the board as well, of course)  .Enjoy ! }
