3. dxc5 Nxc5 4. g4 Bf6 5. Nb3 Ne4 6. Qe1 Qc7 7. gxf5 exf5 8. Nbd4 Ng3
{ 17...Qb6 !  would have been more precise but the text is good enough to maintain some pressure. }
9. Rg1 a6 10. Qb4 Re8 11. Rge1 b5 12. Nb3 Ne4 13. Bxe4 dxe4 14. Nfd4 Be7 15.
Qd2 Qc4 16. Kb1 a5 17. Qe2 Qxe2
{ Now White can reorganize and has more chances of surviving.   26...Bd7 !  27.Qxc4+  bxc4  28.Nd2  Rec8  29.c3  a4  30.a3  Rab8  in comparison would have offered a clear target while keeping the d2 knight at bay. }
18. Nxe2 Rd8 19. Nf4 Kf7 20. Nd4 Bd7 21. Rf1 g6 22. g3 Ra6 23. h4 Rd6 24. Rf2
Bf6 25. Rfd2 Bc8 26. c3 Ba6 27. Kc2 b4 28. cxb4 axb4 29. Nb3 Rxd2+ 30. Rxd2
Rxd2+ 31. Nxd2 Be7 32. Nb3 h6 33. Nd4 g5 34. hxg5 hxg5 35. Nfe2 Kg6 36. Kd2 Bc4
37. b3 Bd3 38. Ke1 Bc5 39. Kd2 Kf6 40. g4 fxg4 41. Ng3 Bd6 42. Nde2 Bxe2 43.
Nxe2 g3 44. Ke1 Kf5 45. Kf1 Kg4 46. Kg2 Bf4 *

